        "title": "Surface Codex final answer candidates in activity",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Emit dashboard/activity `item` events for Codex `phase: \"final_answer\"` answer candidates.\n- Mark earlier candidates as `superseded` and the terminal selected candidate as `selected` while preserving Codex native history and existing partial streaming.\n- Keep answer-candidate activity out of channel progress by setting `suppressChannelProgress: true`; final channel delivery still uses the selected final reply payload.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior or issue addressed: Codex app-server can stream a `phase: \"final_answer\"` candidate, then continue with tool work, then produce a later final answer. The native candidate history is real and should remain visible to operator/debug UIs, but messaging channels should still project one authoritative final answer rather than surfacing candidate activity as normal channel progress.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw repository on macOS, branch `agent/xiaozhua/codex-final-answer-candidates`, using the repository Vitest wrapper and the existing Codex app-server/event-projector and auto-reply pipeline tests.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/src/app-server/event-projector.test.ts --testNamePattern=\"records superseded and selected final-answer candidates without changing the final reply\"\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts --testNamePattern=\"keeps suppressed answer candidates out of channel item progress\"\ngit diff --check\npnpm exec oxlint extensions/codex/src/app-server/event-projector.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/event-projector.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/src/app-server/event-projector.test.ts\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: Focused synthetic Codex stream test constructs `final_answer candidate (\"Draft answer\") → commandExecution tool → final_answer (\"Final answer\")` and verifies the terminal projection plus dashboard/activity events:\n\n```text\nresult.assistantTexts == [\"Final answer\"]\nonPartialReply receives the streamed candidate text and later final text\nactivity item events include:\n  msg-early-final:    status=candidate   progressText=\"Draft answer\" suppressChannelProgress=true\n  msg-early-final:    status=superseded  progressText=\"Draft answer\" suppressChannelProgress=true\n  msg-selected-final: status=candidate   progressText=\"Final answer\" suppressChannelProgress=true\n  msg-selected-final: status=selected    progressText=\"Final answer\" suppressChannelProgress=true\n```\n\nThe channel-pipeline test verifies suppressed answer-candidate item events do not call `onItemEvent` while the run result payload remains:\n\n```text\n[{ text: \"Final answer\" }]\n```\n\nFull related test file output:\n\n```text\nextensions/codex/src/app-server/event-projector.test.ts: 79 passed\nsrc/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts: 183 passed\noxlint: Found 0 warnings and 0 errors\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: Dashboard/activity subscribers can observe two Codex answer candidates for the `final_answer → tool → final_answer` stream, with the earlier candidate marked `superseded` and the final one marked `selected`. Channel progress callbacks suppress those answer-candidate activity records, and the selected final answer remains the only final reply payload.\n\nWhat was not tested: No live Telegram bot message was sent from this PR branch. The channel guarantee is covered at the auto-reply pipeline boundary that Telegram uses for item-progress callbacks and final reply payloads. Raw Codex native event persistence is unchanged by this patch.\n\n## Tests\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/src/app-server/event-projector.test.ts --testNamePattern=\"records superseded and selected final-answer candidates without changing the final reply\"`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts --testNamePattern=\"keeps suppressed answer candidates out of channel item progress\"`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `pnpm exec oxlint extensions/codex/src/app-server/event-projector.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/event-projector.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/src/app-server/event-projector.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts`\n",
